eeds to fill in a ‘Statutory declaration of acknowledgement of parentage’ form and send it to the General Register Office.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@government/documents/digitalasset/dg_176555.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Application form to re-register a child's birth' (PDF, 55KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Application form to re-register a child’s birth’ (PDF, 55KB)</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/documents/digitalasset/dg_176228.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Statutory declaration of parentage' (PDF, 29KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Statutory declaration of parentage’ (PDF, 29KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>If there&rsquo;s been a ‘Declaration of Parentage’</h2>\n\n<p>A Declaration of Parentage is when the court decides who the father of a baby is. You don&rsquo;t need to do anything to change the birth record if there&rsquo;s been a Declaration of Parentage made by a court. The court will tell the General Register Office and the birth will be re-registered. You&rsquo;ll need to order a new birth certificate if you want one.</p>\n\n<h2>Getting a new birth certificate</h2>\n\n<p>You can add the father&rsquo;s name to the birth register by re-registering the birth, but if you want a new birth certificate you&rsquo;ll have to <a href=\"/order-copy-birth-death-marriage-certificate\" title=\"Order a copy of a birth, death or marriage certificate\">order one</a> separately - you don&rsquo;t get one automatically when you re-register the birth.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If the wrong father is named on the current birth certificate, you can <a href=\"/correct-birth-registration\" title=\"Correct a birth certificate\">ask for a correction</a>. That will remove the wrong father’s name. Then you can re-register the birth with the right father’s name.</p>\n</div>\n\n","alternative_title":"Adding a