 leave. </p>\n\n<p>Couples usually have to work at least 16 hours a week each. Only one of you has to work these hours if the other is: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>entitled to carer&rsquo;s allowance </li>\n  <li>in hospital or prison </li>\n  <li>getting certain benefits or credits for disability or illness - eg Disability Living Allowance, Attendance Allowance or a disability premium for Housing Benefit or Council Tax Benefit </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Use the <a href=\"/tax-credits-calculator\" title=\"Tax credit calculator\">tax credit calculator</a> to check if you qualify.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/childcare-tax-credits/how-to-claim","slug":"how-to-claim","order":3,"title":"How to claim","body":"<p>If you&rsquo;re new to tax credits, contact the Tax Credit Helpline for a claim form. It takes up to 2 weeks to arrive. </p>\n\n<p>If you’re already claiming tax credits you don&rsquo;t need a claim form - just call the Tax Credit Helpline to update your claim.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Tax Credit Helpline</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0345 300 3900<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0345 300 3909</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>What you need to know</h2>\n\n<p>You can claim at any time of the year and up to 7 days before you start using childcare (if you&rsquo;re already getting tax credits). </p>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t claim online or download a claim form. </p>\n\n<p>To support your claim, keep records about the carer&rsquo;s registration and the money you pay them (eg receipts or invoices). </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/changes-affect-tax-credits\" title=\"Changes that affect your tax credits\">Report any changes</a> to your childcare because they can affect how much money you get. For example, if you start paying more for your childcare. </p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Tax credits","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/benefits%2Ftax-credits.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes Working Ta