urance number with you when you call.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Child Support Agency Helpline</strong>   </p>\n\n<p><strong>Telephone:</strong> 0845 713 3133 <br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0845 713 8924</p>\n\n<p>Monday to Friday, 8am to 8pm <br />\nSaturdays, 9am to 5pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The helpline will be closed on Christmas Day, Boxing Day and New Year’s Day (and 2 January in Scotland). On Monday 31 December it will close at 5pm.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The people dealing with your case will look at the issues you&rsquo;ve raised. They should respond to you within 15 days.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Contact <a href=\"http://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/index/getadvice.htm\" title=\"Citizens Advice\" rel=\"external\">Citizens Advice</a> or <a href=\"http://findyourmp.parliament.uk/\" title=\"find your MP\" rel=\"external\">your local <abbr title=\"Member of Parliament\">MP</abbr></a> if you need help making your complaint.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Complaints Resolution Team</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re not satisfied with the way that the people dealing with your case have handled things, or if there&rsquo;s been an unreasonable delay, contact the Complaints Resolution Team.</p>\n\n<p>The team will let you know they&rsquo;ve received your complaint within 2 working days. They&rsquo;ll try to sort out your complaint or agree how to sort it out within 15 working days. </p>\n\n<p>If they think it may take more than 15 days to sort out a complaint, they&rsquo;ll keep you regularly updated about progress and agree a timetable with you.</p>\n\n<h2>Complaints Review Team</h2>\n<p>If you&rsquo;re not satisfied with the way that your complaint has been dealt with by the Complaints Resolution Team, or you think there has been an unreasonable delay, you can ask the Complaints Review Team to look at it.</p>\n\n<p>The team will let you know they&rsquo;ve received your complaint within 2 working days. They&rsquo;ll try to sort out your complaint or agree how to sort it out within 15 working days. </p>\n\n<p>If they think it may take more than 15 days to sort out a complaint, they&rsquo;ll keep you regularly updated about progress and agree a timetable with you.</p>\n\n<h2>Independent Case Examiner</h2>\n<p>If you&rsquo;re still unhappy after the Complaints Review Team have looked at the case, you can then <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.ind-case-exam.org.uk\" title=\"Independent Case Examiner\">ask the Independent Case Examiner</a> to investigate - they&rsquo;ll be impartial and this is free. </p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re unhappy with the response from the Independent Case Examiner, you can <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://findyourmp.parliament.uk/\" title=\"contact your MP\">ask your <abbr title=\"Member of Parliament\">MP</abbr></a> to send your complaint to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.ombudsman.org.uk/\" title=\"Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman\">Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman.</a></p>\n\n<h2>If a mistake has been made</h2>\n<p>If there has been a mistake, the <abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr> will:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>apologise</li>\n  <li>explain what went wrong and why</li>\n  <li>make any changes needed to put it right</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;ve been treated particularly badly, you may get compensation, a consolatory payment, or both. However, you don&rsquo;t have a legal right to these.</p>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Having a child, parenting and adoption","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/births-deaths-marriages%2Fchild-adoption.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Legal rights, birth certificates, parental rights and child maintenance","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=births-deaths-marriages%2Fchild-adoption","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/births-deaths-marriages/child-adoption