<a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/individuals/foster-carers.htm\" title=\"Foster care relief\">tax relief</a> for every week (or part week) that a child is in your care. This means you don&rsquo;t have to pay tax on some of your earnings over £10,000.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Age of child</th>\n      <th>Tax relief</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Under 11</td>\n      <td>£200 per child</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Over 11</td>\n      <td>£250 per child</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>Laura is a foster carer for a 14-year-old for the whole of the year and for an 8-year-old for 10 weeks of the year. She doesn&rsquo;t have to pay tax on the first £25,000 she earns:</p>\n\n<p>Tax exemption = £10,000<br />\n+<br />\nChild 1 (52 x £250) = £13,000<br />\n+<br />\nChild 2 (10 x £200) = £2,000  </p>\n\n<p>Total = £25,000</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Pensions</h2>\n\n<p>If you foster, you&rsquo;ll be eligible for <a href=\"/boost-state-pension\" title=\"National Insurance credits\">National Insurance credits</a>, which counts towards your <a href=\"/state-pension\" title=\"State pension\">State Pension</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Benefits</h2>\n<p>Payments for fostering don&rsquo;t affect the amount of benefit you get if the payments come from either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a local council</li>\n  <li>a voluntary organisation</li>\n  <li>a private organisation on behalf of the local council</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If the payments come from somewhere else your benefits may be affected. Read the &lsquo;Fostering and benefit payments factsheet&rsquo; to find out more.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/documents/digitalasset/dg_202526.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Fostering and benefit payments factsheet' (PDF, 140KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Fostering and benefit payments factshe