p>Your child can have 1 or both types of Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr>.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/junior-individual-savings-accounts/opening-an-account","slug":"opening-an-account","order":2,"title":"Opening an account","body":"<p>Only parents or a guardian with parental responsibility can open a Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> for under 16s.</p>\n\n<p>To open a Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> you need to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>choose the type of Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> you want for your child - cash or stocks and shares (or both)</li>\n  <li>choose your <a href=\"/junior-individual-savings-accounts/account-providers\" title=\"Account providers\">account provider</a></li>\n  <li>get an application form from them</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Your child can only have:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>1 cash Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr></li>\n  <li>1 stocks and shares Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Children aged 16 and 17 can open their own Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Accounts\">ISAs</abbr>.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/junior-individual-savings-accounts/account-providers","slug":"account-providers","order":3,"title":"Account providers","body":"<p>You can get a Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> from a range of banks, building societies, credit unions, friendly societies and stock brokers.</p>\n\n<p>Contact any of these direct for more information about how you can open a Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> with them.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/junior-individual-savings-accounts/adding-money-to-an-account","slug":"adding-money-to-an-account","order":4,"title":"Adding money to an account","body":"<p>Anyone can pay money into a Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr>, but the total amount can’t go over £3,600 in a tax year.</p>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong><br />\nIf your child has £1,000 paid into their cash Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> from 6 April 2012 to 5 April 2013, only £2,600 could be paid into their stocks and shares Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> in the same tax year.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can also transfer money between your child’s Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Accounts\">ISAs</abbr> but you can’t do this with:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> and a regular <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr></li>\n  <li>a Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> and a <a href=\"/child-trust-funds/overview\" title=\"Child trust funds\"><abbr title=\"Child Trust Fund\">CTF</abbr> account</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If your child moves abroad, you can still add cash to their Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Who the money belongs to</h2>\n\n<p>Money in a Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> belongs to your child and can’t be taken out until they’re 18, though there are <a href=\"/junior-individual-savings-accounts/if-your-child-is-terminally-ill-or-dies\" title=\"If your child is terminally ill or dies\">exceptions</a> to this.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/junior-individual-savings-accounts/managing-an-account","slug":"managing-an-account","order":5,"title":"Managing an account","body":"<p>Your child&rsquo;s Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> will be in their name, but the parent who opens this is responsible for managing the account and known as the &lsquo;registered contact&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<p>The registered contact is the only person who can:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>change the account, eg from a cash to a stocks and shares Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr></li>\n  <li>change the account provider</li>\n  <li>report changes of circumstances, eg change of address</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Contact your <a href=\"/child-trust-funds/account-providers\" title=\"Account providers\">account provider</a> to do this.</p>\n\n<h2>Children older than 16</h2>\n\n<p>If your child is 16 or older they can:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>become the registered contact for their Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Accounts\">ISAs</abbr></li>\n  <li>open a regular <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>When your child turns 18 they can take out any money in their Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Accounts\">ISAs</abbr>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Accounts\">ISAs</abbr> automatically turn into a regular <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> when the child turns 18.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/junior-individual-savings-accounts/if-your-child-is-terminally-ill-or-dies","slug":"if-your-child-is-terminally-ill-or-dies","order":6,"title":"If your child is terminally ill or dies","body":"<p>The <a href=\"/junior-individual-savings-accounts/managing-an-account\" title=\"Managing an account\">registered contact</a> can take money out of a Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr> early if a child&rsquo;s terminally ill.</p>\n\n<h2>How to take money out</h2>\n\n<p>Contact <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kb5/hmrc/contactus/view.page?record=agUO91tWzfU\" title=\"HMRC: Individual Savings Accounts (ISA) enquiries\">HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>)</a> to let them know that:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your child is terminally ill</li>\n  <li>you want to take money out of their Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You’ll need to provide evidence that your child’s terminally ill.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If your child gets <a href=\"/dla-disability-living-allowance-benefit\" title=\"Disability Living Allowance\">Disability Living Allowance (<abbr title=\"Disability Living Allowance\">DLA</abbr>)</a> because of their illness, tell the <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> when you contact them.</p>\n\n<p>If your child doesn’t get <abbr title=\"Disability Living Allowance\">DLA</abbr>, <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will send you a form for your doctor to complete and return to the <abbr title=\"Child Trust Fund\">CTF</abbr> office, who deal with all terminal illness cases for Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Accounts\">ISAs</abbr> and <a href=\"/child-trust-funds/overview\" title=\"Child Trust Funds\"><abbr title=\"Child Trust Fund\">CTF</abbr> accounts</a>.</p>\n\n<p>For more information, you can call the <abbr title=\"Child Trust Fund\">CTF</abbr> helpline:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Child Trust Fund\">CTF</abbr> Helpline</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0845 302 1470<br />\n<strong>From outside the UK:</strong> +44 1355 359 002<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong>  0845 366 7870</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>What happens next</h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will let you and your account provider know if you can take money out of your child&rsquo;s Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Account\">ISA</abbr>.</p>\n\n<h2>Inheritance</h2>\n\n<p>If your child dies, any money in their Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Accounts\">ISAs</abbr> will be paid to whoever <a href=\"/wills-probate-inheritance/overview\" title=\"Wills, probate and inheritance\">inherits their estate</a>.</p>\n\n<p>This is usually one of the child’s parents but could be your child&rsquo;s husband or wife if they were married.</p>\n\n<h2>What you need to do</h2>\n\n<p>You don’t need to contact <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> but you’ll need to tell your account provider so they can close your child&rsquo;s Junior <abbr title=\"Individual Savings Accounts\">ISAs</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>Your account provider may need need proof to do this, eg a copy of the death certificate.</p>\n\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Having a child, parenting and adoption","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/births-deaths-marriages%2Fchild-adoption.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Legal rights, birth certificates, parental rights and child maintenance","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=births-deaths-marriages%2Fchild-adoption","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/births-deaths-marriages/child-adoption"},"parent":{"title":"Births, deaths, marriages and care","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/births-deaths-marriages.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes civil partnerships, splitting up and Lasting Power of Attorney","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=births-deaths-marriages","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/births-deaths-marriages"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/child-trust-funds.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/child-trust-funds","title":"Child Trust Fund","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-12-04T14:52:31+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/changes-affect-child-benefit.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/changes-affect-child-benefit","title":"Child Benefit if a child or parent dies","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-12-11T17:27:17+00:00"}]},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/legal-rights-for-egg-and-sperm-donors.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/legal-rights-for-egg-and-sperm-donors","title":"Legal rights for egg and sperm donors","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:22:26+00:00","