ple can register the stillbirth:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the occupier of the hospital or house where the stillbirth took place </li>\n  <li>someone who was present at the stillbirth </li>\n  <li>someone who is responsible for the stillborn child </li>\n  <li>the person who found the stillborn child, if the date and place of the stillbirth are unknown</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>What you need to take</h2>\n<p>You need the medical certificate of stillbirth issued by the doctor or midwife.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can arrange a funeral for your baby.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Financial support and taking time off work</h2>\n<p>Following a stillbirth, you&rsquo;re normally entitled to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/statutory-maternity-pay\" title=\"Statutory Maternity Pay\">Statutory Maternity Pay</a> - if you&rsquo;re employed</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/maternity-allowance\" title=\"Maternity Allowance\">Maternity Allowance</a> - if you&rsquo;re not entitled to Statutory Maternity Pay</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/sure-start-maternity-grant\" title=\"Sure Start Maternity Grant\">Sure Start Maternity Grant</a> - if you&rsquo;re on a low income or out of work</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/maternity-leave\" title=\"Maternity Leave\">Maternity Leave</a> - if you&rsquo;re employed</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/paternity-leave-pay-employees\" title=\"Ordinary Statutory Paternity Pay and Leave\">Statutory Paternity Pay</a> - if you&rsquo;re employed</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/paternityleave\" title=\"Paternity Leave\">Paternity Leave</a> - if you&rsquo;re employed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You won&rsquo;t be able to claim Child Benefit.</p>\n\n<h2>Support organisations</h2>\n\n<p>The following organisations give support and advice:</p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.uk-sands.org/\" title=\"Sands charity\">Sands</a><br />\n<a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.tommys.org/\" title=\"Tommy's charity\">Tommy&rsquo;s</a>  </p>\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Death and bereave